<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Glitch on &quot;colour bits&quot; of $2001 on FCEUX?!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12322&amp;p=140249#p140249"><![CDATA[
Support in FCEUX for tint bits is incomplete. It renders the emulated video to a 256-color surface, which is fine for no emphasis but not for multiple emphasis settings, so it only supports about one nonzero set of tint bits per frame.<br /><br />Does it do this in both old PPU and new PPU modes?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Jan 31, 2015 1:56 pm</p><hr />
